Kent Daiber* 

Kent Daiber
Correspondent
Starwood Property Trust
Kent Daiber is a Correspondent at Starwood Property Trust, with responsibility for covering the East Coast. In this role, Mr. Daiber has originated first mortgages and mezzanine loans in excess of $2.2 billion.
Prior to joining Starwood Property Trust in 2012, Mr. Daiber served as Senior Managing Director and Head of Structured Finance for CWCapital LLC, the U.S. real estate finance and investment platform of Caisse de Dépôt et Placement du Québec. At CWCapital, Kent created and managed a business platform encompassing bridge, construction, land and mezzanine loan originations on all commercial property types. Before that, Mr. Daiber was a Senior Vice President at Greenwich Capital Markets, a founding member of Greenwich Capital’s commercial real estate finance group and the head of its structured finance platform. Mr. Daiber previously worked in real estate advisory and merchant banking with Wasserstein Perella & Co. and in New York City residential real estate development at The Related Companies. He began his career as a practicing attorney with Brown & Wood (now Sidley Austin).
Mr. Daiber holds a B.A. degree from Denison University, an MBA from Harvard Business School and a JD from the Vanderbilt University School of Law.
Download vCard 


Jeff Dybas* 

Jeff Dybas
Correspondent
Starwood Property Trust
Jeff Dybas is a Senior Originator/Correspondent at Starwood Property Trust. In this role, Mr. Dybas is responsible for the origination, structuring and execution of senior debt, mezzanine and preferred equity investments across the country in a variety of property types.
Prior to joining Starwood Property Trust in 2016, Mr. Dybas was a Senior Vice President in Bank of America Merrill Lynch’s Commercial Real Estate Group, where he spent six years and originated over $4 billion of bridge, construction, and land loans. Before that, Jeff was a Senior Vice President with Anglo Irish Bank where he spent five years originating and syndicating commercial real estate loans. Previously, Mr. Dybas pursued real estate equity investments, financing, syndication, and portfolio management opportunities with Marathon Asset Management and Bankers Trust (now Deutsche Bank).
Before joining Bankers Trust in 1997, Jeff provided real estate restructuring, valuation, and work-out services with Arthur Andersen. Mr. Dybas began his career in 1991, providing real estate valuation and consulting services with Delta Associates.
Mr. Dybas received a B.A. degree from the University of Virginia, an MBA from The Wharton School, and maintains series 7, 79, and 63 securities licenses.
