Other Senior Executives

Adam Behlman
President and Chief Investment Officer, Real Estate Investing & Servicing
Starwood Property Trust
Adam Behlman is President and Chief Investment Officer of Starwood Property Trust’s Real Estate Investing & Servicing segment. In this role, Mr. Behlman is responsible for overseeing Starwood Property Trust’s commercial mortgage-backed securities and real estate investment platform, as well as leading the company’s wholly owned special servicer, LNR Partners. He previously served as Head of Capital Markets and Chief Risk Officer for LNR.
Prior to joining LNR in 2011, Mr. Behlman served as Head of the Real Estate Finance and CMBS division of UBS. In this role, he was responsible for managing and trading UBS’ legacy CMBS and commercial real estate loan book, while also helping return UBS to the origination, trading and underwriting business. Mr. Behlman previously held a variety of capital markets and real estate roles with firms including Deutsche Bank, Prudential Securities and Deloitte.
Mr. Behlman holds a B.A. degree from Queens College, CUNY, in both accounting and information systems and economics.

Larry Brown
President
Starwood Mortgage Capital
Larry Brown is President of Starwood Mortgage Capital. In this role, Mr. Brown oversees all lending and securitization activities for the platform. He previously co-founded Archetype Mortgage Capital in 2011, and served as President of the company—which was renamed Starwood Mortgage Capital in 2013.
Prior to joining Archetype, Mr. Brown was a Co-Founder, Managing Director and Chief Operating Officer of AllBridge Investments, an investor in the commercial real estate capital markets. Before that, Mr. Brown started Deutsche Bank Mortgage Capital, L.L.C., a subsidiary of Deutsche Bank, and served as President and CEO of the company. Mr. Brown previously served as President of WMF Capital Corp., and was a Managing Director of Commercial Real Estate Finance at First Union National Bank (now known as Wells Fargo), where he co-founded the bank’s real estate capital markets group. Before that, he was a Senior Vice President in the real estate finance group at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette, and an Associate at the law firms of Baker & McKenzie and Mudge, Rose, Guthrie, Alexander & Ferdon, where he specialized in real estate banking and real estate finance law.
Mr. Brown holds a B.A. degree with honors in political science from Tufts University and a JD from Georgetown University School of Law.

Zachary Tanenbaum
Director, Investor Relations
Starwood Property Trust
Zachary Tanenbaum is Head of Investor Relations for Starwood Property Trust. In this role, Mr. Tanenbaum is responsible for cultivating and managing the company’s relationships with the global investment and analyst communities.
Prior to joining in Starwood Property Trust in 2014, Mr. Tanenbaum served as a Senior Analyst at Wesley Capital Management, a long/short real estate securities hedge fund. In this role, he generated investment ideas across the REIT, real estate operating company, specialty finance and homebuilding sectors. He previously served in senior sell-side equity research positions at FBR Capital Markets and MLV & Co.
Mr. Tanenbaum received a B.S. degree from Cornell University and an M.S. degree in real estate, with a concentration in finance and investment, from New York University.




